race.comment: LULU DARLING (11) is a seasoned mare with good form for this level at her best. Turned in a great run fresh when tries to lead throughout but run down late. Fitter and will take catching again. THREE MUSKETEERS (10) looks to be edging towards a win and looks a serious danger. Runner-up latest over 1400m and will be tough to stop here. GURU TWO (9) is a super honest galloper who returned with an eye-catching second at Wagga when he found the line strongly. Trained here and will go close second-up. KING INCANTO (6) was midfield last time but ran very well here two back and gets a chance to bounce back. BRITISH POET (2) has ability and is on the quick back up after finishing seventh at Gundagai a couple of days ago. Worth keeping safe.
